I think the fix is in the wrong place. We should fix the underlying vector. I was able to fix the problem with a small change to BaseRepeatedValueVector.BaseRepeatedMutator:

``` java
@Override
    public void startNewValue(int index) {
      while (offsets.getValueCapacity() <= index) {
        offsets.reAlloc();
      }
      offsets.getMutator().setSafe(index+1, offsets.getAccessor().get(index));
      setValueCount(index+1);
    }
```

We shouldn't need to make any change in the writer.
